  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; required levels are met or exceeded at each gradation. Decision: Accepted. Hemolysis predictions remain below the absolute clinical threshold across all five flow-speed combinations. Methodology follows the power-law hemolysis damage model discussed in the literature (see referencesIdentifier).",
